$ SAS options

Most options can be set with an → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/statements/options[options] statement, in → Companies-Products/SAS/files/configuration[configuration files] or with the
`SASV9_OPTIONS` environment variable. Some options can only be set when the
system initializes.

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/autoexec

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/center

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/cmplib

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/config

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/cpucount

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/date

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/dflang

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/dmssyncheck

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/formdlim

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/locale

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/logparm

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/macrogen

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/metaautoresources

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/notes

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/number

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/linesize

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/mautosource

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/mprint

